File: Load-shedding is expected to continue until 5am on Monday morning. JOHANNESBURG - Another dark morning as load-shedding continues. On Saturday Eskom implemented stage 3 load-shedding up from stage 2. LOAD-SHEDDING: Schedules, info, and how it affects you The power utility said stepped up load-shedding was due to the shortage of capacity and in order to replenish emergency reserves. Load-shedding is expected to continue until 5am on Monday morning. The struggling power utility has asked everyone to use electricity sparingly and to switch off their geysers during peak hours.